sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2116028
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: bxb1 integrase under the control of nitric oxide and AHL responsive AND gate
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: AND gate, bxb1 with moderately fast degradation tag. Useful for constructing logic gates. esabox can be replaced to create other AND gates with NO responsiveness [link to our lactate AND gate].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Asli Azizoglu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2116011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: AND gate regulated by Nitric Oxide and 3OC6HSL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: rAND gate created by placing one esabox as roadblock, and one esabox right before the first norR binding site of the PnorV promoter. This second esabox is added to create competitive binding between norR and esaR, and improve AND gate behaviour.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Asli Azizoglu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2116026
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: bxb1 integrate that can invert a sequence flanked by the att sites it recognises.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Asli Azizoglu
